  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Buyer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Duties and Responsibilities </strong></u></p><ul><li>Assisting in purchasing department in day-to-day activities such as accurate input and issue of PO</li><li>Building relationships with suppliers and negotiating with them for the best price, quantities and delivery timescales</li><li>Arranging incoming material shipment, handling RTV, administrative task such as record keeping and RFQ for costing roll up </li><li>Processing requisitions and updating management on the status of orders</li><li>Updating inventory and managing stock levels</li><li>Arranging transport of goods and tracking orders to ensure timely delivery</li><li>Understanding the target market and analysing trends in order to make informed buying decisions</li><li>Work with Expeditor on vendors’ delivery and submission of supporting documents</li><li>Documentation, Filing and Record Keeping</li><li>Perform ad hoc duties as assigned</li></ul><p><u><strong>Position Requirements</strong></u></p><p><strong>Education Requirements:</strong> Diploma in Supply Chain, Business, Engineering or related education </p><p><strong>Experience Level Requirements</strong>: Minimum 2 years work experience\n<br /><strong>Skills Desired:</strong></p><ul><li>Intermediate Proficiency in Microsoft Office</li><li>Good command of the English Language</li><li>Knowledge in ERP System will be an added advantage</li><li>Able to work independently with minimum supervision</li><li>Interpersonal skills, particularly in negotiating</li><li>Ability to cope with pressure and adapt to situations</li><li>Analytical skills</li><li>Good team player, responsible and keen to learn</li><li>Good interpersonal & communication skills</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
